<ul>
<li>Remember our <a href="">Risk Management Plan<span>Risk a lot to save a lot, Risk a little to save a little, Risk nothing to save that which is already lost.</span></a></li>
<li>Always approach to scene cautiously</li>
<li>Place apparatus to protect the scene and to maintain a buffer from the vehicle</li>
<li>Practice offensive traffic management</li>
<li>Halt all traffic if smoke is blowing across the roadway</li>
<li>Always wear your PPE</li>
<li>Establish incident zones (hot, warm, cold) at every incident 
<li>Beware of <a href="">Vehicle Fire Hazards<span>Air bags, gas-filled cylinders, alternative fuels</span></a></li>
<li>Choose the right attack line</li>
<li>Use the proper approach to the vehicle</li>
<li>Secure the vehicle with wheel chocks</li>
<li>Be aware of the weather – if its freezing you may need a load of ice melt/sand to make the roadway safe</li>
<li>Make sure the scene is left clean\safe for the general public</li>
</ul>

